# Environment and Configuration

## Current Setup

`env.sh` is **optional**. It no longer sets compiler variables ŌĆö bundled SQLite
compiles with any standard C compiler. Source it only if you want the convenience
path exports.

```bash
source env.sh   # optional ŌĆö sets UFORGE_* path variables
```

## Environment Variables

### Build-time (no longer required)
```bash
# CC / CXX ŌĆö no longer need to be set to gcc-13.
# Any C/C++ compiler found on PATH works.
```

### Runtime / Optional
```bash
export LEMONADE_URL="http://localhost:13305/api/v1"  # Lemonade Server for embeddings
export UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR="./defaults/schemas"       # Override schema directory
export UFORGE_DATA_FILE="./defaults/data/memory.json" # Override data file
export RUST_LOG=info                                # Log verbosity
```

### Module-specific logging
```bash
export RUST_LOG=u_forge_core::graph::storage=debug,u_forge_core::ai::embeddings=info
```

## Path Resolution

### Schema Directory (checked in order)
1. `$UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR`
2. `./defaults/schemas`
3. `../defaults/schemas`

### Data File (checked in order)
1. `$UFORGE_DATA_FILE`
2. `./defaults/data/memory.json`
3. `../defaults/data/memory.json`

## Lemonade Server Configuration

Lemonade Server provides all AI inference (embedding, reranking, chat, STT, TTS) via
an OpenAI-compatible HTTP API. u-forge.ai does **not** fall back to a local model if
Lemonade is unavailable ŌĆö it returns a clear error with instructions.

```bash
# Install on Linux (snap)
sudo snap install lemonade-server

# Pull required models
lemonade-server pull embed-gemma-300m-FLM    # embeddings (NPU, 0.62 GB) ŌĆö default embedding model
lemonade-server pull whisper-v3-turbo-FLM    # transcription (NPU, 1.55 GB)
lemonade-server pull bge-reranker-v2-m3      # reranking (GPU/CPU)

# Start the server
lemonade-server serve

# Verify health (also shows which models are currently loaded in RAM)
curl http://localhost:13305/api/v1/health

# Point u-forge.ai at it (optional ŌĆö localhost:13305 is auto-discovered)
export LEMONADE_URL="http://localhost:13305/api/v1"
```

`lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()` resolves the server URL in this order:
1. `GET http://localhost:13305/api/v1/health` ŌĆö probed with 2 s timeout
2. `GET http://127.0.0.1:13305/api/v1/health` ŌĆö explicit IPv4 loopback
3. `LEMONADE_URL` environment variable ŌĆö accepted as-is, no liveness check

Returns `None` when no server is found. Setting `LEMONADE_URL` is optional when
Lemonade Server runs on its default port.

### Lemonade API Endpoints in Use

| Endpoint | Method | Provider / Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/v1/models` | GET | `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()` ŌĆö catalog discovery |
| `/system-info` | GET | `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()` ŌĆö installed backends |
| `/api/v1/health` | GET | `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()` + manual verification |
| `/api/v1/load` | POST | `load_model()` ŌĆö load a model before inference |
| `/api/v1/embeddings` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeProvider` (`lemonade/embedding.rs`) |
| `/api/v1/audio/transcriptions` | POST (multipart) | `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` (simple, no GPU lock) |
| `/api/v1/audio/transcriptions` | POST (multipart) | `LemonadeSttProvider` (GPU-managed) |
| `/api/v1/audio/speech` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeTtsProvider` (`lemonade/tts.rs`) |
| `/api/v1/chat/completions` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeChatProvider` (`lemonade/chat.rs`) |
| `/api/v1/reranking` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeRerankProvider` (`lemonade/rerank.rs`) |

> **Note on the two transcription providers:** `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider`
> has no GPU resource management ŌĆö suitable for NPU FLM whisper and standalone use.
> `LemonadeSttProvider` integrates with `GpuResourceManager` to prevent contention
> when LLM inference is running concurrently on the same GPU. Both are constructed
> via `ProviderFactory::build` with `Capability::Transcription`.

## Database Location

`KnowledgeGraph::new(db_path)` opens (or creates) a SQLite database at
`<db_path>/knowledge.db`. The directory is created automatically if it does not
exist.

```bash
# Default in CLI demo: a TempDir is used (ephemeral).
# For a persistent database, pass an explicit path:
cargo run --example cli_demo
# or set UFORGE_DATA_FILE / UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR to customise import sources.
```

## Build Commands

```bash
cargo build --workspace                                                              # Build (first time ~30s for bundled SQLite)
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1                                           # Run all tests (no server required)
cargo run --manifest-path crates/u-forge-core/Cargo.toml --example cli_demo         # Run demo with Foundation data
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1 --nocapture               # Tests with debug logging
```

## Cross-Platform

| OS | C compiler needed | Lemonade install |
|---|---|---|
| Ubuntu / Debian | `apt install gcc` (usually pre-installed) | `snap install lemonade-server` |
| macOS | Xcode CLT (`xcode-select --install`) | `.pkg` from GitHub releases |
| Windows | MSVC (Visual Studio Build Tools) or MinGW | `.exe` installer from releases |

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| `openssl-sys` build error | Install `pkg-config libssl-dev` (Ubuntu) or `openssl` (macOS brew) |
| `Lemonade Server not available` error | Run `lemonade-server serve` and set `LEMONADE_URL` |
| `lemonade-server pull` fails | Check disk space; retry; verify network access |
| Schema not found | Check `$UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR`, verify `.json` files exist |
| Database locked | Only one process should open the same `knowledge.db` at a time |
| Dimension mismatch (future sqlite-vec) | Ensure embedding model matches vector column dimensions |
| Transcription returns error immediately | Model not pulled ŌĆö run `lemonade-server pull whisper-v3-turbo-FLM` |
| Transcription error: "Could not open audio data" | Audio bytes are empty or the file is not a valid audio format |
| Whisper not loaded in RAM | First transcription call triggers model load; subsequent calls are fast. Check `GET /api/v1/health` to see which models are in RAM. |